Naming components
=================

You can name any Abjad component.

<abjad>
flute_staff = Staff(construct.scale(4))
flute_staff.name = 'Flute'
violin_staff = Staff(construct.scale(4))
violin_staff.name = 'Violin'
staff_group = StaffGroup([flute_staff, violin_staff])
score = Score([staff_group])
</abjad>

Component names make it easy to find components later. ::

   scoretools.find(score, 'Flute')
   [Staff{4}]

Component names do not appear in musical output.

<abjad>
write_ly(score, '1') <hide
</abjad>

Use the instrument interface to add instrument names.

<abjad>
flute_staff.instrument.name = 'Flute '
violin_staff.instrument.name = 'Violin '
</abjad>

Instrument names do appear in musical output.

<abjad>
write_ly(score, '2') <hide
</abjad>
